---
// src/pages/speculation/index.astro
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Speculative Hypotheses"
  description="Alternative hypotheses exploring the role of gangliosides in unexplained medical phenomena."
>
  <!-- Warning Banner -->
  <section class="bg-amber-500 text-amber-950 py-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <p class="font-bold text-lg">‚ö†Ô∏è SPECULATIVE CONTENT</p>
      <p class="text-sm">These pages present alternative hypotheses for discussion and further investigation. They are not peer-reviewed or established science.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900 to-slate-800 text-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <nav class="text-sm text-slate-400 mb-4">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-white">Speculation</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Thinking Outside the Box</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-3xl">
        The ganglioside system is largely unknown in clinical medicine. These pages explore 
        alternative hypotheses for unexplained medical phenomena through the lens of 
        glycosphingolipid biology.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      
      <div class="bg-slate-100 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Why Speculate?</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700">
          Many medical mysteries remain unsolved because researchers look in familiar places. 
          Gangliosides represent a <strong>"hidden system"</strong> that determines which cells 
          are targeted by pathogens, toxins, and autoimmune responses. By considering ganglioside 
          biology, we can generate new hypotheses that might explain previously puzzling phenomena.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Speculative Hypotheses</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Havana Syndrome -->
        <a href="/speculation/havana-syndrome/" class="block bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="text-4xl">üëÇ</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Havana Syndrome: A Ganglioside Hypothesis?</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mb-3">
                Could the mysterious auditory symptoms reported by U.S. diplomats in Cuba (2016-2017) 
                be explained by H3N2 influenza's affinity for GM3 gangliosides in cochlear hair cells?
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs rounded">H3N2</span>
                <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs rounded">GM3</span>
                <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-pink-100 text-pink-800 text-xs rounded">Cochlea</span>
                <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-800 text-xs rounded">2016-2017</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>

        <!-- Future: More speculative pages could be added here -->
        <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-dashed border-slate-300 rounded-lg p-6 text-center text-slate-500">
          <p class="text-lg mb-2">More hypotheses coming...</p>
          <p class="text-sm">
            Other unexplained phenomena that might involve ganglioside biology: 
            post-viral syndromes, chronic fatigue, long COVID vestibular symptoms, etc.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-400 p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">The Scientific Method</h3>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm">
          Speculation is the first step in the scientific process. These hypotheses are 
          presented not as established facts, but as <strong>testable ideas</strong> that 
          could be investigated with proper research. If you are a researcher interested 
          in exploring these connections, we welcome collaboration.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Navigation -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-slate-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Established Hypotheses</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
        For the main hypothesis on Pandemrix and narcolepsy (with stronger evidence):
      </p>
      <a href="/hypothesis/" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-slate-800 transition-colors">
        The Axonal Highway Hypothesis ‚Üí
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
